Canada House Prices Rose 1.3% in July, Teranet Index Shows

-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 
2011-09-28T13:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/canada-house-prices-rose-1-3-in-july-teranet-index-shows.html
Canadian  house prices  rose 1.3
percent in July, gaining for an eighth consecutive month,
according to the  Teranet-National Bank  Composite House Price
Index.  Housing prices rose 5.3 percent in July from a year
earlier, according to a report released today by National Bank
Financial. The index rose to 146.51, a new high.  Calgary led gains in July, with prices advancing 2.3
percent.  Home prices  in Toronto advanced 1.7 percent during the
month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
